      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Decrease in avalanche danger as the temperature drops. Early morning: The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust and will hardly soften at all. In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. Crampons or ski Crampons are useful, especially on traverses and very smooth and hard slopes. <br/> Until midday the weather will be partly cloudy in some localities. <br/> In the afternoon the activity of moist and wet avalanches will only slowly increase. The near-surface layers of the snowpack can be released in isolated cases by winter sport participants in particular in extremely steep terrain. <br/> In particular in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place and at the base of rock walls more small and, in isolated cases, medium-sized natural wet avalanches are possible. <br/> The conditions are generally favourable for ski touring.",
        "highlights": "The danger of moist and wet avalanches will increase but remain within the current danger level."
