      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The spring-like weather conditions gave rise to rapid settling of the snowpack. <br/> This situation gave rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 2500 m. <br/> The amount of snow is subject to significant local variations. <br/> Below the tree line hardly any snow is lying on southeast and southwest facing slopes. <br/> Especially on the colder slopes above the treeline, in the valley basins and headlands that have been less affected by stormy winds in recent weeks, there is excellent snow cover. <br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on steep shady slopes."
      },
